The paper deals with a wireless communication system with multiple antennas and nonlinear power amplifiers, which is a common topic in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses precoding techniques to mitigate multi-user interference, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of power amplifiers and power efficiency is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
